Reviewing all my sunscreens ☀️

I’ve used more than 50 sunscreens, and here I’m breaking down a few of my current ones.

Starting with the @lasheildindia Matte Sunscreen which has SPF 50 PA++++. It’s a mineral sunscreen containing 25% zinc oxide. As expected, the texture is thick and greasy and leaves a white cast — makes me look like a disco ball throughout the day. I used this during one of my beach vacations, and the protection was commendable. I barely got any tan or sunburn. It’s water and sweat-resistant, so it’s best for heavy-duty protection over long hours.

@lightup.beauty sunscreen — the texture is creamy but turns watery once you start blending it into your skin. It feels super refreshing with no heavy feeling and gives a matte finish. Plus, it contains 1% ceramide and vitamin C.

@niveaindia Shine Control Sunscreen — the whole reason I bought this was because I read somewhere on Reddit that it’s an exact dupe of the Biore UV Aqua Rich Watery Essence. So I kinda got influenced and bought it, but the next moment I realized it’s not what I expected. First of all, it pills on my skin no matter what I do. The alcohol smell is too strong for my liking. And after using it for a while, it makes me look oily and dull, and I sweat a lot when I wear it.

@thehyphen.co All I Need sunscreen — I love it! It’s perfect for the Indian climate. I feel like this would suit every skin type as the texture is really creamy and hydrating, but not oily at all.

@thankyoufarmer Water Sunscreen — it’s super hydrating without being oily. Every time I use this, I get compliments about what I’ve applied because it gives a beautiful, healthy sheen to my skin. This one’s definitely going to suit all skin types.

@dr.sheths Haldi & Hyaluronic Acid Sunscreen — it has a yellow tint to it. By now, you probably get that any sunscreen that gives a dewy finish is my fave, and this one’s no exception. If you're looking for a dupe for the Thank You Farmer sunscreen, please go for this one — they both give a really similar finish.
